(287, 37, 0, 1, '2018-02-14 18:04:16', '2018-02-14 15:27:29', 37, 'en', 1, 1, 'Information', 'Information', NULL, '<div class="section page-content bg-white">\n<div class="container">\n<div class="row">\n<div class="col-md-12">\n<div id="page-31" class="clearfix post-31 page type-page status-publish hentry">\n<div class="page-content">\n<p>Dear Runner!<br /> We welcome you to THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE. Here you&rsquo;ll find all important information. Please read carefully and completely. In case you have any questions, please feel free to get touch with us any time. We wish you a good and healthy training and all the best and a great result for your race.</p>\n<p><strong>Date</strong><br /> Saturday 21 April 2018</p>\n<p><strong>Location</strong><br /> Batumi / Ajara / Georgia<br /> Would you like to get a first impression of Batumi? Please look <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xIe9NnJ2YDE" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>!</p>\n<p><strong>Host and Organizer</strong><br /> Hotel Colosseum Marina<br /> 16, Sherif Khimshiashvili Street<br /> 6015 Batumi / Ajara / Georgia<br /> Phone: +995 422 24 44 00<br /> Website: <a href="http://www.colosseummarina.ge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.colosseummarina.ge</a><br /> E-Mail: <a href="mailto:info@colosseummarina.ge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">info@colosseummarina.ge</a></p>\n<p><strong>Event Contact</strong><br /> E-Mail: <a href="mailto:info@batumi-marathon.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">info@batumi-marathon.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>AIMS Membership</strong><br /> The event has applied for full AIMS membership of the halfmarathon. The halfmarathon racecourse has been measured by an AIMS A-grade measurer on Monday 13 November 2017.</p>\n<p><strong>Distance, Starting Time, Agegroup and Participation Fee</strong></p>\n<div class="wpsm-comptable-wrap">\n<table id="wpsm-table-1" class="wpsm-comptable  wpsm-comptable-responsive stacktable large-only">\n<thead class="wpsm-thead wpsm-thead-default">\n<tr><th>Distance</th><th>Starting Time</th><th>Agegroup</th><th>Fee</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class="wpsm-tbody">\n<tr>\n<td>circa 10 km FunRun</td>\n<td class="">19.10 h</td>\n<td class="">14 and older</td>\n<td class="">20 GEL / ca. 8 US$ / ca. 7 EUR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>21,1 km HalfMarathon</td>\n<td class="">19.30 h</td>\n<td class="">16 and older</td>\n<td class="">40 GEL / ca. 16 US$ / ca. 14 EUR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1.000 m KidsRun</td>\n<td class="">18.45 h</td>\n<td class="">10 &ndash; 13</td>\n<td class="">Free of Charge</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>500 m KidsRun</td>\n<td class="">18.30 h</td>\n<td class="">6 &ndash; 9</td>\n<td class="">Free of Charge</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Services Included in Your Participation Fee</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Race organized corresponding to international AIMS rules and regulations</li>\n<li>Unique THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE running shirt, as long as stock lasts</li>\n<li>Race-course free of traffic</li>\n<li>Bib number with integrated time keeping chip</li>\n<li>Medal</li>\n<li>Net-time-keeping</li>\n<li>Certificate to print out</li>\n<li>Professional presenters at the start- and finishline</li>\n<li>Entertainment on the course</li>\n<li>Refreshments on the course and after the finishline</li>\n<li>Medical service on the course and in the start- and finish-area</li>\n<li>Victory ceremony</li>\n<li>Tombola</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Prices Halfmarathon Race</strong><br /> Finisher of all races are awarded a special medal.</p>\n<div class="wpsm-comptable-wrap">\n<table id="wpsm-table-3" class="wpsm-comptable center-table-align wpsm-comptable-responsive stacktable large-only">\n<thead class="wpsm-thead wpsm-thead-default">\n<tr><th>Price for Over All Winners of Halfmarathon</th><th>&nbsp;</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class="wpsm-tbody">\n<tr>\n<td class="">Over All Winner Men</td>\n<td>2.000 Euro</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Over All Second Men</td>\n<td>1.500 Euro</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Over All Third Men</td>\n<td>1.000 Euro</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Over All Winner Women</td>\n<td>2.000 Euro</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Over All Second Women</td>\n<td>1.500 Euro</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Over All Third Women</td>\n<td>1.000 Euro</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="wpsm-comptable-wrap">\n<table id="wpsm-table-4" class="wpsm-comptable center-table-align wpsm-comptable-responsive stacktable large-only">\n<thead class="wpsm-thead wpsm-thead-default">\n<tr><th>Prices for Winners of Masterclass (Over all winners of age groups 40 and older)</th><th>&nbsp;</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class="wpsm-tbody">\n<tr>\n<td class="">Masterclass Winner Men</td>\n<td>powered and presented by tbd</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Masterclass Second Men</td>\n<td>powered and presented by tbd</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Masterclass Third Men</td>\n<td>powered and presented by tbd</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Masterclass Winner Women</td>\n<td>powered and presented by tbd</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Masterclass Second Women</td>\n<td>powered and presented by tbd</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">Masterclass Third Women</td>\n<td>powered and presented by tbd</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<br /> The victory ceremony for the halfmarathon will take place after the race at about 22.15 h in the start- and finish-area\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Registration, Time Keeping, Results and Ranking</strong></p>\n<p>Please register here: <a href="/registration/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Registration</a></p>\n<p>Online registration is open until Friday 13 April 2018 24.00 h.</p>\n<p>All runners aged 18 and over can participate in the races. If you are 14 &ndash; 15 years old you can participate in the circa 10-km-run, if you are 16 -17 years old you can participate in both the circa-10-km-run and the halfmarathon. In any case please send us a formless written consent of the legal representative. A membership in a sportsclub or federation is not necessary.</p>\n<p>If you register prior to 11 March 2018 you will get a personalized bib number with your name on.<br /> Time keeping is a net-time-keeping by an electronic chip integrated in your bib number. Time keeping and participant administration is operated by MIKA Timing.</p>\n<p>After the race you&rsquo;ll find your result and your personal certificate to print out on our website.<br /> Ranking according to AIMS / IAAF rules and regulations. The age group of an athlete is determined by his date of birth.</p>\n<p><strong>Group Age (male / female)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>U 16 14 &ndash; 15 (No halfmarathon, only circa 10 km)</li>\n<li>U 18 16 &ndash; 17</li>\n<li>U 20 18 &ndash; 19</li>\n<li>Main Class 20 &ndash; 29</li>\n<li>Seniors 30 &ndash; 34</li>\n<li>Seniors 35 &ndash; 39</li>\n<li>Seniors 40 &ndash; 44</li>\n<li>Seniors 45 &ndash; 49</li>\n<li>Seniors 50 &ndash;54</li>\n<li>Seniors 55 &ndash; 59</li>\n<li>Seniors 60 &ndash; 64</li>\n<li>Seniors 65 &ndash; 69</li>\n<li>Seniors 70 &ndash; 74</li>\n<li>Seniors 75 &ndash; 79</li>\n<li>Seniors 80 &ndash; 84</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>PickUp of Starting Documents and Late Registration</strong></p>\n<p><em>Indoor Tennis Court of the Hotel Colosseum Marina</em></p>\n<p>PickUp of your starting documents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Thursday 19 April 2018 12.00 h &ndash; 20.00 h</li>\n<li>Friday 20 April 2018 12.00 h &ndash; 20.00 h</li>\n<li>Saturday 21 April 2018 10.00 &ndash; 16.00 h</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Late Registration</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Thursday 19 April 2018 12.00 h &ndash; 20.00 h</li>\n<li>Friday 20 April 2018 12.00 h &ndash; 20.00 h</li>\n<li>Saturday 21 April 2018 10.00 &ndash; 14.00 h</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please pay your late registration in cash. There is an additional handling fee of 5 GEL for any late registration.</p>\n<p><strong>Transfer of the Starting Number to Another Runner</strong></p>\n<p>You can transfer your start number to another runner. To do this, please present a formless authorisation, signed by the surrender and filled in with your data (name, address, date of birth, E-Mail, phonenumber), the surrenders confirmation mail and your personal ID or your passport as you collect the starting documents.</p>\n<p>Please note: You can transfer your starting number from HalfMarathon to HalfMarathon respectively from FunRun to FunRun. You can transfer from HalfMarathon to FunRun. However, unfortunately there is no partly refund of the registration fee. If you wish to transfer from FunRun to HalfMarathon we charge you 20 GEL. Please pay in cash.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Thursday 19 April 2018 12.00 h &ndash; 20.00 h</li>\n<li>Friday 20 April 2018 12.00 h &ndash; 20.00 h</li>\n<li>Saturday 21 April 2018 10.00 &ndash; 14.00 h</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There is an additional handling fee of 5 GEL for any transfer. Please pay in cash.</p>\n<p><strong>Changing Rooms, Baggage Room and Shower </strong></p>\n<p>We provide changing rooms in the indoor tennis court of the Hotel Colosseum Marina.</p>\n<p>We provide baggage rooms in the indoor tennis court of the Hotel Colosseum Marina. Please put the baggage sticker, which comes with your starting documents, on your starterbag prior to handing it to our volunteers.</p>\n<p>Please note: The luggage storage accepts without any exception only the official starterbags with the bib number sticker attached. Our luggage storage is guarded. However, the host assumes no liability.</p>\n<p>We are planning to provide showers for all our runners.</p>\n<p><strong>Travel to Batumi and Parking</strong></p>\n<p>Please arrange your jouney to Batumi yourself. Every good travel agency will support you. Limited parking is available on the premises. You can also park in the streets around the hotel.<br /> Please note, however, that there may be a delay due to the road blocking on the raceday from 16.00 h to 22.30 h. These delays also affect buses and taxis.</p>\n<p><strong>Accomodation</strong></p>\n<p>The Hotel Colossuem Marina offers you great packages. After you have completed your online registration you may visit the Hotel Colloseum Marina website. Here you&rsquo;ll find special packages for you as participant of our races.</p>\n<p><strong>Race Courses</strong></p>\n<p>All information and interesting facts about our great race courses through the city of Batumi you&rsquo;ll find in the section <a href="/race-courses/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Race Courses</a>!</p>\n<p><strong>Refreshment Points on the Race Course</strong></p>\n<p>circa 10 km FunRun<br /> There are no refreshment points on this course. After you have crossed the finishline we provide a good mineral water and bananas.</p>\n<p>21,1 km HalfMarathon<br /> We provide a good mineralwater and bananas every 5 kilometers.</p>\n<p><strong>Medical Care</strong><br /> For medical emergencies, a professional medical service is available on the course and at the start- and finish-area.</p>\n<p><strong>Liability</strong></p>\n<p>The organizer&rsquo;s liability for damage to the participants is limited to intent and gross negligence. This does not apply to damages resulting from injury to life, body or health, which result from a negligent breach of duty on the part of the organizer or a deliberate or negligent breach of duty by a legal representative or vicarious agent of the organizer. The host has taken out liability insurance.</p>\n<p><strong>Miscellaneous</strong></p>\n<p>The participant declares that he is sufficiently trained to participate in this competition, is physically healthy and his health has been confirmed by a doctor. The organizer reserves the right to refuse runners without stating any reasons. The starting fee is not refunded.</p>\n<p>The participant agrees that the data mentioned in his registration, the photographs, films, and interviews made by him during his participation in the THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE may be used in all media without compensation claims.<br /> The event takes place in all weather conditions. However, the organizer reserves the right, in the case of &ldquo;imminent danger&rdquo;, e.g. heat, storms, force majeure, terror, etc., to terminate the race prematurely without any claim for any reimbursement of the participation fee.</p>\n<p>Unless otherwise described, the competition rules of the IAAF and AIMS apply.<br /> This tender has been compiled carefully. If changes or additions are necessary, they will be communicated in good time on this website.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Sporty greetings from Batumi<br /> Your THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE Organizing Team</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class="wpml-ls-statics-post_translations wpml-ls">This post is also available in: <span class="wpml-ls-slot-post_translations wpml-ls-item wpml-ls-item-ge wpml-ls-first-item wpml-ls-last-item wpml-ls-item-legacy-post-translations"><a href="/old/ge/%e1%83%98%e1%83%9c%e1%83%a4%e1%83%9d%e1%83%a0%e1%83%9b%e1%83%90%e1%83%aa%e1%83%98%e1%83%90/"><img class="wpml-ls-flag" title="Georgian" src="/old/wp-content/uploads/flags/ge.png" alt="ge" /><span class="wpml-ls-native">Georgian</span></a></span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, 'information', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'information, სიცოცხლის, წიგნი', 'Information', 0, NULL),
(288, 38, 0, 1, '2018-02-14 18:10:09', '2018-02-14 15:27:28', 38, 'ge', 1, 1, 'მარშრუტი / რუკა', 'მარშრუტი / რუკა', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'courses', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'მარშრუტი, რუკა, სიცოცხლის, წიგნი', 'მარშრუტი / რუკა', 0, NULL),
(289, 38, 0, 1, '2018-02-14 18:10:09', '2018-02-14 15:27:28', 38, 'en', 1, 1, 'Courses', 'Courses', NULL, '<p>Dear Runner!<br /> Flat &ndash; Fast &ndash; Unforgettable! That was our idea as we designed your race course. We have developed a great course for you through the wonderful city of Batumi. You will enjoy the entire Boulevard all along the Black Sea coast, great views to the surrounding mountains of the Caucasus, the old town, the harbour and last but not least the fascinating Miracle Park &ndash; experience the <em>Alphabetic Tower</em> and meet <em>Ali and Nino</em>. The core event is the halfmarathon. The 21,1-km-course is one loop. The start- and finish-area is on the Boulevard right next to the <a href="http://colosseummarina.ge/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hotel Colosseum Marina</a>.</p>\n<div class="wpsm-comptable-wrap">\n<table id="wpsm-table-2" class="wpsm-comptable ">\n<thead class="wpsm-thead wpsm-thead-default">\n<tr><th>Distance</th><th>Starting Time</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class="wpsm-tbody">\n<tr>\n<td class="">circa 10 km FunRun</td>\n<td class="">19.10 h (Time limit 1:25 h)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">21,1 km HalfMarathon</td>\n<td class="">19.30 h (Time limit 2:45 h, finish line closes at 22.15 h)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">1.000 m KidsRun</td>\n<td class="">18.45 h</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="">500 m KidsRun</td>\n<td class="">18.30 h</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Please get picture of the halfmarathon race course <a href="https://www.gpsies.com/map.do?fileId=qtpfvzcbacefnvfz" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Also you can take a look at this <a href="https://www.relive.cc/view/r9215597176" target="_blank" rel="noopener">animation</a> of the race track. Enjoy!</p>\n<p>If you do not manage to make it within the time limit, please complete the race on the sidewalk as the race course is released to traffic.</p>\n<p>THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE has applied for full <a href="http://www.aims-worldrunning.org/aims.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AIMS</a> membership of the halfmarathon. The halfmarathon racecourse has been measured by an official A-grade-measurer of AIMS on 13 November 2017. Please have a look at the official <a href="/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/TGBNR-MEAS-CERT-2017.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">measurement certificate</a>.</p>\n<p>The course is clearly marked with a blue line on the surface of the road. There will be kilometer marks every kilometer. Professional cyclists will guide you on the course. Most of the course is asphalt. There are some passages of very small cobblestones, which are very easy to run and will not slow you down.</p>\n<p>For the duration of the race the course is free of traffic and exclusively reserved for you as participant of THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE. Please attend the orders of the police and our volunteers.</p>\n<p>Every five kilometers (km 5 &ndash; km 10 &ndash; km 15 &ndash; km 20) you will find refreshment points. Here we offer you a good mineral water and bananas cut into pieces. In case of hot weather conditions (above +25&deg;C) we provide additional water stations as well as showers. Also you will find refreshments after you have finished your race.</p>\n<p>For medical emergencies, a professional medical service is available on the course and at the start- and finish-area. Please have a look from time at your fellow runners. If you find them in a bad condition, please report to the nearest medical station.</p>\n<p>There will be a lot of entertainment in the start- and finish-area as well as hot spots on the course. So even if you are not an active runner you are cordially invited to join and become part of a great event, to enjoy yourself and to cheer for all athlets.</p>\n<p>The expected weather in Batumi on your raceday respectively in April according to statistics:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>+ 15,6&deg;C average daytime temperature</li>\n<li>4,9 h average sunshine duration</li>\n<li>14 rain days in April</li>\n<li>76% average humidity</li>\n</ul>\n<p>[Source: Wikipedia (German) Batumi / wetterkontor.de]</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Sporty greetings from Batumi<br /> Your THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE Organizing Team</p>\n</blockquote>', NULL, NULL, 0, 'courses', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'courses, სიცოცხლის, წიგნი', 'Courses', 0, NULL),
(290, 39, 0, 1, '2018-02-14 18:10:38', '2018-02-14 15:27:26', 39, 'ge', 1, 1, 'პირობები', 'პირობები', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'terms', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'პირობები, სიცოცხლის, წიგნი', 'პირობები', 0, NULL),
(291, 39, 0, 1, '2018-02-14 18:10:38', '2018-02-14 15:27:26', 39, 'en', 1, 1, 'Terms', 'Terms', NULL, '<p>Dear Runner!</p>\n<p>Here you find the Terms of Participation. We know nobody likes to read such fine-printed stuff. However, unfortunately we can not waive it. So we kindly ask you to read this part carefully and completely. It won&rsquo;t hurt. Thank you very much for your attention.</p>\n<p><strong>The general terms and conditions of participation described below are valid for all participants who participate in one of the competitions within the framework of THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE.</strong></p>\n<p>These conditions of participation govern the relationship between the participants and the organizer. They are occasionally subject to changes. They are part of the agreement between the organizer and the participant in their valid version. Changes made taking into account the legitimate interests of the participants and which are published by the organizer in the internet or in written form will become an integral part of the Terms of Participation.</p>\n<p>The age groups valid for this halfmarathon are listed under General Information.</p>\n<p>All runners aged 18 and over can participate in the races. Younger participants may participate with a formless written consent of the legal representative. A membership in a sportsclub or federation is not necessary.</p>\n<p>All runners who are in possession of an official start number of THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE are entitled to start. The bib number is not transferable and is to be worn in full size on the front of the running dress. Changing or covering the lettering and/or sponsorship logos is not permitted and leads to the disqualification. Runners without a bib number are refered to leave the race by the marshals.</p>\n<p>You can transfer your start number to another runner. To do this, please present a formless authorisation, signed by the surrender and filled in with your data (name, address) and your personal ID or your passport as you collect the starting documents.</p>\n<p>By registering for&nbsp;THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE I acknowledge the exclusion of any liability of the organizers for damages of all kinds. I will neither fight against the organizers and sponsors of&nbsp;THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE or against the city of Batumi or their representatives to assert claims for injuries and damages of any kind which might arise in connection with the participation in THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE. I know that the event takes place in every weather. However, the organizer reserves the right, in the case of &ldquo;imminent danger&rdquo;, e.g. heat, storms, force majeure, terror, etc., to terminate the race prematurely without any claim for any reimbursement of the participation fee.</p>\n<p>I declare that I have trained enough to participate in this race, are physically healthy and my medical condition has been confirmed by a doctor. I also assure that I am not using doping drugs, that my birth year and other personal data are correct, and that I will only pass my start number within the framework of the above regulation. I agree that my personal data, the photographs, films, and interviews I have made during my participation in&nbsp;&nbsp;THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE may be used on my own without any remuneration claims. I assure that my date of birth indicated on registration is correct and I will not pass my start number to any other person. I am aware of the fact that I can be disqualified if I change the official start number in any way, in particular parts of it.</p>\n<p>Participation in a contest of&nbsp; THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE using other sports equipment (such as walking sticks/In-Line-Skaters or similar) is not permitted. Sports equipment of any kind, which can affect the safety or health of the participants or visitors of the event, are not allowed to participate in the event. For safety reasons, participation with wheelchairs and/or so-called &ldquo;handbikes&rdquo; is only possible after consultation with the organizer. An accompaniment by bicycles, inline skaters and other means of transport or animals is not allowed and results in the disqualification of the respective runners!</p>\n<p>According to the IWR (International Competition Rules) 144, the use of sound reproducing devices of all kinds, e.g. MP3 players, SmartPhones etc., is prohibited throughout the competition area during the competition. Inobservance results in disqualification. Equipment which is used to measure heart rate, speed or step counting may be carried along for these purposes. Therefore, please do not wear headphones for your own protection and protection of your followers. In the competition one should be attentive and be aware that, for example, by listening to music and cutting off from the environment. The consequences of not being able to perceive dangerous situations, e.g. approaching rescue services, accompanying vehicles, cyclists, dogs, etc. should not be underestimated! Enjoy the special and motivating atmosphere of a race with our presenter, the music and the spectators who have come to cheer you up.</p>\n<p>The organizer shall announce organisational measures to the participants prior to the start of the event. The instructions of the organizer and the personnel indicated accordingly must be followed. In the case of infringements which may disturb the course of the event or jeopardize the safety of the other participants, the organizer shall be entitled to declare the eventual disqualification from the event and/or a disqualification. Legally binding declarations may only be submitted by the organizer&rsquo;s authorized persons. This group of persons also includes the members of the medical services attending the event, who can also prevent the participation or continuation of participation in the event in the event of appropriate health signs to protect the participant.</p>\n<p><span id="result_box" class="" lang="en"><span class="">Is the organizer, without intention or gross negligence, in cases of force majeure </span><span class="">or required by official directives or for security reasons, conducting changes in </span>organizing or canceling the event, there is neither an entitlement to a refund of the organizing fee nor a claim compensation<span class=""> of the organizer regarding the participant.</span></span></p>\n<p>In the case of my non-participation (illness, business travel, etc.), there is no entitlement to a refund of the organizing fee, unless the organizer is responsible for my non-participation.</p>\n<p>Registration is mandatory and subject to charges. If participants do not attend, there is no entitlement to a refund of the participation fee.</p>\n<p>I acknowledge that the organizers of <span class="gbnr_sp">THE GREAT BATUMI NIGHT RACE</span> reserve the right to exclude me from the event if the above obligations are proven.</p>\n<p>Note according to the Data Protection Act: Your data will be stored electronically.</p>', NULL, NULL, 0, 'terms', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'terms, სიცოცხლის, წიგნი', 'Terms', 0, NULL);
